The paper presents techniques for maintaining subgraph frequencies in a dynamic graph, which is a problem in graph data structures and algorithms. The paper also mentions applications in Bioinformatics and Social Networking research, indicating a potential connection to data mining and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Other likely sub-categories include cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
